            <h2>Ligao City</h2>
            <h3>Where Good Things Happen</h3>

            <img src="<?= $this->webroot ?>theme/weatherph/img/tourism/ligaoCity1.png" alt="">

            <p>The City of Ligao, located at the heart of the third district of Albay just below the majestic Mayon Volcano, holds a great potential for tourism and investments. It is naturally gifted with caves, hills, lakes, and coastal areas perfect for nature lovers and trekking enthusiasts.</p>
            <p>Ligao is a decade-old city, once dubbed as a richly-endowed developing town in Albay. It is now considered as the trade cen- ter for the nearby municipalities of Pioduran, Oas, Guinobatan, Polangui and Libon.</p>
            <p>Legend tells that Ligao was coined with the corruption of the word ticau, once an abundant tree whose poisonous leaves were popularly used to catch fish in rivers or creeks. It was also believed that the name came from licau which means to take the long way around or to turn away from the ordinary or usual route. Lastly, most believed that it came from the Tagalog word ‘ligaw’ meaning to court or win a lady’s love. This idea was based on the common knowledge that the place was then known for its beautiful maidens.</p>
            <p>The City envisions to be an internationally competitive trade and educational center of the third district of Albay by year 2018. Its mission is to “turn Ligao City into a community of love, peace, equality, and prosperity; anchored on the following core values: love of God, love of country, love of community, vision- driven, innovativeness, resilience, transparency, culture of excel- lence, and discipline.”</p>
            <p>Aside from the panoramic view of Mayon Volcano, Ligao is gifted with various breathtaking sceneries. One is the becoming more popular Kawa-Kawa Hill Natural Park. It has become a famous ecotourism destination especially for devotees of the Divine Mercy. The Carmelite nuns of the Holy Trinity have put up a monastery and life-sized images of the Station of the Cross that are spread out upward towards the top of the Hill (“without a top”).</p>
            <p>The Hill has become a favorite venue for religious activities during Lenten Season, Christmas, and Three Kings which have become annual traditions for the visitors of Kawa-Kawa. Ligao City is also a home to various spring resorts that offer continuous flowing spring water for a cool deep relaxation.</p>

