            <h3>Ligao City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1 .Trek on top of the Kawa-Kawa Hill and Natural Park and Visit the Divine Mercy Oratory and Monastery of the Carmel- ite Nuns of the Holy Trinity. The place is a reflection of the residents’ religiosity, with life-sized sculptures of the Stations of the Cross placed on the way to the top. Souvenir shops are also found at the foot of the Hill.</li>
                <li>2. Taste Ligao’s distinct native delicacies. Among others, the City boasts of the rice puto con macapuno that is made up of two layers of puto — one colored purple, the other is white, with macapuno filling in the middle. This can be bought along the highway of Paulog, Ligao City and also at the City Market.</li>
                <li>3. Buy pili nuts in Edsel Morato Pili Sweets that is located in McKinley Street, Dunao, Ligao City. It is said that pili nuts that are prepared in Ligao stand out as one of the best in the Bicol region.</li>
                <li>4. Dance with Walt Disney characters in giant floats every December 25 during the Christmas Mainstreet Parade competition. It is one of the activities for the feast day of Ligao City’s Patron Saint, St. Stephen, the Protomartyr, which coincides with the Christmas Season.</li>
                <li>5. Learn from Ligao City’s innovative and outstanding local governance practices, programs, and projects. The local government was awarded as the top performing city in the component city category for 2010, given by the Department of Interior and Local Government in their Local Governance Performance Management System (LGPMS) Report.</li>
            </ol>
