            <h4>How to get there</h4>
            <p>From Manila, Ligao City is located 525 kilometers, a 10-12 hour ride via bus. It is 27 kilometers from the provincial capitol of Albay and 30 kilometers from Legazpi City.</p>
            <p>From Manila, it is a 45-minute ride by plane via Legazpi City and an hour-ride from Legazpi City.</p>
            <h4>Best time to visit</h4>
            <ol>
                <li>1. December is the best time to visit Ligao City because of (1) The Lighting of the giant Christmas tree on the first Sunday of December, (2) Patiribayan sa Ligao, a traditional amateur and dance contest every Friday night starting October, (3) Christmas Cheers, a nightly program starting December 16 (in time with the Start of the Misa de Gallo), the (4) Mainstreet Parade, a parade of Walt Disney characters depicted by groups of students, teachers and barangay officials and (5) the Fiesta Celebration on December 26.</li>
            </ol>
